result.adr_address: Shop 322, 3/F, Landmark Atrium, Central, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: Shop 322, 3/F, Landmark Atrium, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Urban Bakery Works

reviews.text: Heard good reviews on their croissant so came round for breakfast one day. Food was beyond expectation. Found seating overlooking the center of landmark and they have fun napkin! Love their avocado smoothie! They have a good variety of hot breakfast and croissants, price is reasonable for the portion served and location. I would come back again.

This place is great, in I mean in particular their different croissants. Really tasty and abundant and a very friendly staff. They have done their best to make the place nice being situated in a weird corner inside a mall, but it cannot loose the makeshift feel completely. Point for trying though, maybe real cups would help a lot. The runny egg yolk custard and cheese overflow of the croissants got me so occupied that I could not care less about the seating arrangement anyway.
They do a good range of lunches that all tastes great. Plus they do reasonable coffee. Although it can be a challenge getting a seaf around lunch time.
Good quick food without being fast food. Best happy hour in Central with BOGO on beers, ciders, and wines from 5-8pm on weekdays.
Food is excellent there. BUT their service sucks. All of the staffs there have an attitude problem.
